body:
While porting SVUnit to Verilator I stumbled upon a subtle issue. Function calls in SV are allowed without braces - (). Looks like Verilator does not like that style. Sample error:

```log
%Error: vw_vlt_issue_1.sv:11:42: Found definition of 'get_start_tag_contents' as a FUNC but expected a variable
   11 |     result = $sformatf("%s<%s>", indent, get_start_tag_contents);
      
```


Thanks for taking the time to report this.

Can you attach an example that shows the issue?  (Must be openly licensed, ideally in test_regress format.)

Commands:
```sh
verilator --binary vw_vlt_issue_1.sv -DBUG
verilator --binary vw_vlt_issue_1.sv (Works)
```

```verilog
class c;
  function string get_start_tag_contents;
  endfunction : get_start_tag_contents

  local function string as_string_with_indent(string indent);
    string result;
    string tmp_s;
   `ifndef BUG
    result = $sformatf("%s<%s>", indent, get_start_tag_contents());
  `else
    result = $sformatf("%s<%s>", indent, get_start_tag_contents);
  `endif // BUG
  endfunction : as_string_with_indent
endclass : c
module top;
  c c_0;

  initial begin
    c_0 = new();

    #100 $finish (2);
  end
endmodule : top


```

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?
> Verilator 5.005 devel rev v5.004-75-gbe53eec5c

What OS and distribution are you using?

> WSL, Ubuntu

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?

> Yes please, though my Lex/yacc expertise is read-only so far.
